                  <interp inst="t18241202-99-crimeloc544" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-99-crimeloc544" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-99-off542 t18241202-99-crimeloc544"></join>. The prisoner was in their service - it was his duty to <rs id="t18241202-99-deflabel545" type="occupation">deliver beer, and receive the money</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-99-defend642 t18241202-99-deflabel545"></join> for it - he was to book the beer and pay the money to me every evening. On the <rs id="t18241202-99-cd546" type="crimeDate">26th of October</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-99-off542 t18241202-99-cd546"></join> he went out with some beer for Mr. Wright, a grocer, in Oxford-street. I have the book here in which he ought to have made the entry, but there is no such entry, nor has he paid me 5 s. 6 d. as received of Mr. Wright on that day. He was taken into custody about a fortnight afterwards - he had not made any mention of this circumstance - there are entries of beer delivered to other customers but none to Mr. Wright.</p>
